To install:
    cd src/pito
    ./configure
    make
    make install

Options can be set at configure time see:
    cd src/pito
    ./configure --help

Alternatively you can set options after configuring with cmake:
    cd src/pito
    ./configure
    ccmake .obj

Please see the website for documentation:
    http://chilon.net/pito

If you have meow you can "cd doc && make" to generate the website locally.
